# .understandignore - patterns for files/dirs to exclude from analysis
# Syntax: same as .gitignore (globs, # comments, ! negation, trailing / for dirs)
#
# Built-in defaults are always excluded unless negated by the analyzer:
# node_modules/, .git/, dist/, build/, __pycache__/, *.lock, binary assets, etc.
#
# Uncomment project-specific patterns below if you want to exclude them later.

.understand-anything/
*.db

